    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix undefined behavior in CSI-RS scheduling due to missing constant definition\n\n### Summary\nThe NR UE MAC scheduler's CSI-RS reception scheduling function was exhibiting undefined behavior due to a missing constant definition. The function `nr_schedule_csirs_reception()` references `NR_maxNrofCSI_ResourceConfigurations` which was not defined anywhere in the codebase, causing compilation failures or runtime issues depending on compiler settings.\n\nAdditionally, there was a potential issue with negative modulo operations in the periodicity calculation that could cause CSI-RS resources to be scheduled incorrectly when the current slot index was less than the configured offset.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/nr/nr_common.h`: Added missing constant definitions for CSI-related parameters based on 3GPP TS 38.331 specification\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/nr_ue_scheduler.c`: Fixed modulo calculation in periodicity checking to handle negative values properly in both CSI-RS and CSI-IM scheduling functions\n\nThe issue manifested as CSI-RS resources not being scheduled for reception at the expected slots, particularly when the slot offset configuration caused negative values in the periodicity calculation. This led to incorrect channel state information reporting and potential performance degradation.\n"
}